        <h2 class="font-semibold text-4xl text-white pb-4 text-center">Why Become a CFI?</h2>
        <div class="text-white px-6 lg:pl-0 lg:pr-8 p-text">
          <p class="pb-5">
            The primary reason pilots choose to become a Certified Flight Instructor (CFI) is the pursuit of experience and the accrual of flight hours. In the aviation industry, especially for highly sought roles like commercial airline pilots, meeting ATP minimums and specific flight hours is required. Many pilots opt for flight instruction as their first pilot job which offers rapid progress in flight time accumulation. Guiding students in the art of safe and proficient aircraft operation not only imparts essential skills but also solidifies the knowledge garnered during your personal flight training journey. Over time, flight instructors become seasoned aviators, proficiently equipped to both train and endorse fellow pilots for FAA practical evaluations.
          </p>
