      <div class="text-black px-10 p-text lg:max-w-xl">
        <p class="pb-5">
          Meeting the Federal Aviation Regulations (FAR/AIM) requirements is essential on the path to becoming a Certified Flight Instructor (CFI) at Ideal Aviation. To obtain your instructor's certificate, aspiring CFIs must hold a Commercial Pilot Certificate and have logged a minimum of 250 flight hours, including specific experience in different aircraft categories. Successful completion of a CFI ground school and passing the Fundamentals of Instruction (FOI) knowledge test are also crucial milestones. At Ideal Aviation, we provide structured training to ensure you meet these requirements and equip you with the teaching skills and aviation expertise needed to inspire and mentor future pilots.
        </p>
        <p class="pb-5">
          <span class="font-bold font-sans text-2xl">Choose Ideal Aviation and Begin Your Certified Flight Instructor Training Today</span>
        </p>
        <p class="pb-5">
          Ideal Aviation is the place for pilots becoming a Certified Flight Instructor (CFI). Our staff and team of seasoned CFI professionals provides unparalleled mentorship and support, ensuring you receive the best guidance on your journey to your CFI certification. Our modern fleet of well maintained aircraft is specially equipped to meet the demands of CFI training. Located conveniently near downtown St. Louis, Ideal Aviation offers easy access for local and visiting candidates. Join Ideal Aviation, where our commitment to CFI excellence becomes your key to a successful career in aviation education.
        </p>
        <p class="grid place-items-center pb-10">
          <%= link_to "CONTACT US",  contact_path, data: { turbo: false }, class: "btn-primary"%>
        </p>
